#: ../../source/collaborate/mention-people.rst:7
msgid ""
"When you want to get the attention of specific Mattermost users, you can "
"use @mentions. Mattermost supports the following types of @mentions:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/collaborate/mention-people.rst:9
msgid "`@username <#username>`__"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/collaborate/mention-people.rst:10
msgid "`@channel <#channel-and-all>`__"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/collaborate/mention-people.rst:11
msgid "`@all <#channel-and-all>`__"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/collaborate/mention-people.rst:12
msgid "`@here <#here>`__"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/collaborate/mention-people.rst:13
msgid "`@groupname <#groupname>`__"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/collaborate/mention-people.rst:14
msgid "`@customusergroupname <#customusergroupname>`__"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/collaborate/mention-people.rst:18
msgid ""
"If you forget to mention someone in a message, editing the existing "
"message to add an @mention won't trigger new @mention notifications, "
"desktop notifications, or notification sounds."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/collaborate/mention-people.rst:19
msgid ""
"Mattermost supports mentions for names that include accents (also known "
"as diacritics). Names like Zoë, Jesús, Sørina, François, André, Jokūbas, "
"Siân, KŠthe, or Fañch are returned in autocomplete results."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/collaborate/mention-people.rst:22
msgid "@username"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/collaborate/mention-people.rst:24
msgid ""
"You can mention a teammate by using the *@* symbol plus their username to"
" send them a mention notification."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/collaborate/mention-people.rst:26
msgid ""
"Type *@* to bring up a list of team members who can be mentioned. To "
"filter the list, type the first few letters of any username, first name, "
"last name, or nickname."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/collaborate/mention-people.rst:30
msgid ""
"Using Mattermost in a web browser or the desktop app, you can also press "
"the :kbd:`↑` and :kbd:`↓` arrow keys to scroll through entries in the "
"list, and press :kbd:`ENTER` on Windows or Linux, or :kbd:`↵` on Mac, to "
"select the person to mention. When selected, the username replaces the "
"full name or nickname."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/collaborate/mention-people.rst:32
msgid ""
"The following example sends a special mention notification to Alice, "
"whose username is **alice**. The notification alerts her of the channel "
"and message where she was mentioned. If Alice is away from Mattermost and"
" has email notifications turned on, she'll receive an email alert of her "
"mention along with the message text."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/collaborate/mention-people.rst:38
msgid ""
"If the person you mentioned doesn't belong to the channel or the team, a "
"system message is posted to let you know, and you're given the option to "
"add the person to the channel. You are the only one who can see this "
"message."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/collaborate/mention-people.rst:41
msgid "@channel and @all"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/collaborate/mention-people.rst:43
msgid ""
"You can mention an entire channel by typing ``@channel`` or ``@all``. All"
" members of the channel receive a mention notification that behaves the "
"same way as if the members had been mentioned personally. If used in Town"
" Square, it notifies all members of your team."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/collaborate/mention-people.rst:45
msgid ""
"You can ignore channel-wide mentions in specific channels in the "
"**Channel Menu > Notification Preferences > Ignore mentions for @channel,"
" @here and @all**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/collaborate/mention-people.rst:51
#: ../../source/collaborate/mention-people.rst:62
msgid ""
"If a channel has five or more members, you may be prompted to confirm "
"that you want notifications sent to everyone in the channel."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/collaborate/mention-people.rst:54
msgid "@here"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/collaborate/mention-people.rst:56
msgid ""
"You can mention everyone who is online in a channel by typing ``@here``. "
"This sends a desktop notification and push notification to members of the"
" channel who are online. It's counted as a mention in the sidebar. "
"Members who are offline don't receive a notification. When they return to"
" Mattermost they won't see a mention counted in the channel sidebar. "
"Members who are away receive a desktop notification only if they have "
"notifications set to **For all activity**, and they won't see a mention "
"counted in the sidebar."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/collaborate/mention-people.rst:64
msgid ""
"You can ignore channel-wide mentions in specific channels by enabling the"
" **Channel Menu > Notification Preferences > Ignore mentions for "
"@channel, @here, and @all** option."
msgstr ""

